            , Constable. I keep a Cook's-shop, in St. Sepulchre's Parish. About a Fortnight ago, Fidzar and the Beadle, and two or three others, came to dine at my House; and after Dinner, the Beadle charged me with Fidzar, who had surrendered himself; and I went with him before Justice Robe, where he impeached the Prisoners and Will. Travers, otherwise Moco Jack, and 
